Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Slice @demi-baguette{1} crosswise into 8 rounds (16 rounds for 4); spread out on a #baking sheet{} and drizzle with @olive oil{2%tablespoon}. Toast on top rack until golden brown, ~{5-10%minutes}. (For 4, if necessary, divide rounds between two #baking sheets{}; toast on top and middle racks.) (Reserve #baking sheet{} for Step 5.)

Place @ricotta cheese{4%ounce} in a #small bowl{}; whisk in a large drizzle of olive oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread ricotta onto toasted baguette rounds; drizzle with @honey{4%teaspoon} and sprinkle with @walnuts{1/2%ounce}.

Serve with your favorite beverage for snacking while you prepare the rest of the meal.

> Prefer to serve the crostini with the main course? Toast now and assemble right before serving!

== Mashed Potatoes ==

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and halve @brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Strip @rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings). Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1} until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4).

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in empty #pot{} used for potatoes over medium heat. Add garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add drained potatoes and @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}; mash until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed with a #potato masher{}. Season with salt and pepper. Top with @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}.

== Panko and Brussels Sprouts ==

While potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #medium, preferably nonstick, pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Toss Brussels sprouts on baking sheet used for crostini with a large drizzle of olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Carefully transfer to bowl with toasted panko; toss to combine. Season with half the minced rosemary, salt, and pepper.

== Beef Tenderloin ==

While Brussels sprouts roast, pat @beef tenderloin filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in pan used for panko over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}. Wipe out pan.

== Sauce ==

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add minced shallot; cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1}, @fig jam{1}, @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings), any resting juices from beef, and remaining minced rosemary to taste. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide mashed potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and beef between plates. Top beef with sauce and serve.

Serve @white chocolate raspberry swirl cheesecake{2} for dessert.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.